HEADWORD: lingenberry
<hw>lingenberry</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>low evergreen shrub
(<spn>Vaccinium vitis-idaea</spn>) of high north temperate regions of
Europe and Asia and America bearing red edible berries.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cowberry, mountain cranberry, lingonberry,
lingberry, foxberry, <spn>Vaccinium vitis-idaea</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

